			<p>HOW DOES CELL <br/>PHONE DISCO WORK?</p>
		</Text>
		

			<Text x="40" y="400" id="overlay0-text" class="overlaytext" height="400">
				<p>Behind the wall there are small antennae and sensors that can detect how much Electromagnetic Radiation is being broadcast in the specific wavelengths that are commonly used for cell phone communication in our area (836MHZ, 1732MHz, and 1880 MHz). <br/><br/> 

				Based on the strength of the signal being received at each sensor, controllers inside the wall send a signal to each light telling it how brightly to glow.  Brighter lights mean a stronger signal.  White light indicates a very strong signal.
				</p>
